sql:
SELECT e.experiment_name
FROM experiments e
WHERE e.status = 'completed' AND e.created_by = 2;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS completed_training_runs
FROM training_runs
WHERE status = 'completed';

external_knowledge:
- 'Successfully concluded their training phases' refers to training runs with a status of 'completed'.;
- Average metric values are calculated as the mean of all metric values for each experiment.;
- Experiments with any incomplete training runs are excluded from the results.;
